XTREEMFS is a distributed and replicated file system for the
Internet. Clients and servers can be distributed world-wide.
XtreemFS allows you to mount and access your files via the internet
from anywhere. You can also easily replicate your files across
data-centers to reduce network consumption, latency and increase
data availability.

Once installed you have to define uuids for the available services,
mrc and osd. I haven't quite figured out what exactly to do here yet,
but it is related to uuidgen and the "uuid = " lines in the config
files.

xtreemfs requires apache-ant and the jdk package from /extra